rm production contribution driven by fusion of\ngluons for neutrino energies $E_{\\nu} \\gtrsim 300$ GeV. For electron and muon\nneutrinos both the mechanisms lead to a similar production rates and their\nseparation seems rather impossible. On the other hand, for $\\nu_{\\tau} + {\\bar\n\\nu}_{\\tau}$ neutrino flux the recombination is further reduced making the\nmeasurement of the IC contribution very attractive.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 17 Oct 2022 09:39:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 27 Oct 2022 08:33:44 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 31 Oct 2022 08:20:38 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 14 Dec 2022 09:36:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-15"}
